x4freetext: High-purity natural uranium metal rod of diameter
2.74 mm and length 5 mm weighing 5.6 g
ORTEC 40% HPGe detector coupled to a PC based
8K channel analyzer. The resolution of the detector
system was 2.0 keV full width at half maximum (FWHM)
at the 1332.0 keV gamma line of Co-60.
Fission products were measured by using a
recoil catcher and off-line gamma-ray spectrometric
The bremsstrahlung beam was produced by
impinging a pulsed electron beam on a light
watercooled cylindrical tungsten target of 5 cm
diameter and 5mm thickness. The electron linac was
operated with a pulse repetition rate of 25 Hz and a
pulse width of 2.5 Microsecond. The peak current
during irradiation was 100mA with an average current
